cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.DB, cs.AI, cs.SY

This paper is likely to belong to the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) because it presents a framework for verifying differential privacy in Bayesian machine learning algorithms. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with probabilistic programming languages and Bayesian inference. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.DB (Databases) as it deals with data privacy. The paper also involves techniques from cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) in its approach to verifying privacy using a relational refinement type system.
